The 28-year-old man, who works at an unnamed school in Birmingham, is also accused of sending indecent images of himself, West Midlands Police said. The suspect was originally arrested on May 9 but was rearrested this morning at his home in the city after police received additional information. He has been suspended by the school and remains in police custody. In a statement, the force said: “We’re investigating sexual assault accusations against a teacher at a Birmingham school. “It’s alleged the 28-year-old man assaulted four different girls and sent indecent images of himself." “He was initially arrested on May 9 on suspicion of sexual assault and released on police bail with conditions including not to have unsupervised contact with children." “However, we moved to arrest the man again in the early hours of this morning (Saturday) at his home in Birmingham having received additional information."  